.TH "__skb_gso_segment" 9 "__skb_gso_segment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__skb_gso_segment \- Perform segmentation on skb.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" __skb_gso_segment
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "netdev_features_t features "  ","
.BI "bool tx_path "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
buffer to segment
.IP "features" 12
features for the output path (see dev->features)
.IP "tx_path" 12
whether it is called in TX path

This function segments the given skb and returns a list of segments.

It may return NULL if the skb requires no segmentation.  This is
only possible when GSO is used for verifying header integrity.

Segmentation preserves SKB_GSO_CB_OFFSET bytes of previous skb cb.
